sequenceDiagram
    title Panglot — Card Generation Pipeline

    actor User
    participant App as App (Actix-web :8080)
    participant State as AppState
    participant Pipe as Pipeline~L~
    participant GenCtx as GeneratorContext
    participant LLM as OpenAiClient → Gemini
    participant Parse as AnyCard::parse~L~
    participant Val as CardValidator
    participant FeatCtx as FeatureExtractorContext
    participant TTS as TtsGenerator (edge-tts)
    participant IPA as IpaGenerator (epitran)
    participant Late as LatePostProcessor
    participant Deck as DeckBuilder~P~

    Note over User,Deck: ══ HTTP POST /api/generate or /api/export ══

    User ->>+ App: POST /api/generate<br/>{ language, node_id, card_model_id,<br/>  difficulty, user_profile, user_prompt }
    App ->> State: dispatch_pipeline!(language)
    State ->>+ Pipe: generate_cards_batch(node_id, req, llm_sem, pp_sem)

    Note over Pipe,LLM: ── Step 1: Build Prompt ──
    Pipe ->> GenCtx: new(language, skill_node, node_path, request)
    GenCtx ->> GenCtx: generate_prompt()<br/>• Language directives<br/>• Skill path + node instructions<br/>• Difficulty & user profile<br/>• JSON schema for card model
    GenCtx -->> Pipe: LlmRequest

    Note over Pipe,LLM: ── Step 2: LLM Call 1 — Content Generation ──
    Pipe ->>+ LLM: chat_completion(request)<br/>temperature: 0.8<br/>response_schema: CardModel + ExtraFields
    LLM -->>- Pipe: JSON response (array of cards)

    Note over Pipe,Val: ── Step 3: Parse & Validate ──
    loop For each card in JSON array
        Pipe ->> Parse: parse~L~(card_model_id, json_str)
        Parse -->> Pipe: (AnyCard, L::ExtraFields)
        Pipe ->> Val: validate(language, model, extra)
        alt Validation fails
            Val -->> Pipe: Err(feedback_message)
            Note over Pipe,LLM: ── Step 4: Retry with feedback ──
            Pipe ->> LLM: chat_completion(original + feedback)
            LLM -->> Pipe: Corrected JSON
            Pipe ->> Parse: re-parse
        else Validation passes
            Val -->> Pipe: Ok(())
        end
    end

    Note over Pipe,IPA: ── Step 5: Parallel Processing (per card) ──

    par Feature Extraction (LLM Call 2)
        Pipe ->> FeatCtx: new(language, skill_node, card_json)
        FeatCtx ->> FeatCtx: generate_prompt()<br/>• Extraction directives<br/>• PoS descriptions<br/>• Card content
        FeatCtx -->> Pipe: LlmRequest
        Pipe ->>+ LLM: chat_completion(request)<br/>temperature: 0.0
        LLM -->>- Pipe: FeatureExtractionResponse<br/>{ pedagogical_explanation, features[] }
    and Early Post-Processing (subprocesses)
        Pipe ->>+ TTS: process(language, card_id, model, extra)
        TTS ->> TTS: tokio::process::Command<br/>edge-tts → .mp3
        TTS -->>- Pipe: EarlyPostProcessResult { audio_file }
        Pipe ->>+ IPA: process(language, card_id, model, extra)
        IPA ->> IPA: tokio::process::Command<br/>epitran → IPA string
        IPA -->>- Pipe: EarlyPostProcessResult { ipa }
    end

    Note over Pipe,Late: ── Step 6: Late Post-Processing ──
    Pipe ->> Late: process(language, model, extra, &mut metadata)
    Late -->> Pipe: Ok(())

    Note over Pipe,Deck: ── Step 7: Assemble Result ──
    Pipe ->> Pipe: CardMetadata~P~ {<br/>  card_id: UUID,<br/>  skill_id, pedagogical_explanation,<br/>  features, ipa, audio_file<br/>}
    Pipe -->>- App: Vec~GeneratedCard~ { model, metadata }

    alt /api/generate
        App ->> State: store cards in generated_cards
        App -->> User: GenerateResponse { success, cards[], message }
    else /api/export
        App ->>+ Deck: new(deck_name)
        loop For each GeneratedCard
            App ->> Deck: add_card(model, metadata)
        end
        App ->> Deck: export_apkg(output/node_id.apkg)
        Note over Deck: ZIP archive:<br/>• collection.anki2 (SQLite)<br/>• media JSON<br/>• audio files (0, 1, 2...)
        Deck -->>- App: .apkg file
        App -->> User: File download
    end

    Note over User,Deck: ══ Other Endpoints ══

    User ->> App: GET /api/tree?lang=polish
    App -->> User: SkillTree JSON (nodes hierarchy)

    User ->> App: POST /api/preview-prompt
    App -->> User: { messages[], temperature, max_tokens }

    User ->> App: GET /api/card-models
    App -->> User: [ClozeTest, WrittenComprehension, OralComprehension]

    User ->> App: POST /api/add-node
    App ->> State: find parent → append child SkillNode
    App -->> User: Updated tree
